Edward Doyle v. Thomas W. Mizner. Submitted Oct. 7. Ed. E. Kane for the motion. Geo. W. Moore against.

Time — Return of writ of error.

A writ of error may be made returnable in “not less than twenty days.” Sup. Court Buie 10. Held, that the time runs from and excludes the date of issue and includes the return day, and that a' writ issued August 30 was properly made returnable September 19.

Motion to dismiss writ of error.

Denied Oct. 8.
